From: Immortal OPI CM5 overlay
Subject: rockchip: rk3588s-orangepi-5: SPL try eMMC (sdhci) before microSD

Orange Pi CM5 modules boot from on-module eMMC on &sdhci. The carrier SD
slot is &sdmmc. The stock u-boot.dtsi only listed &sdmmc, so SPL never probed
eMMC when no SD card was inserted (MMC1 voltage select errors, then abort).

Try &sdhci first, then &sdmmc, matching the generic rk3588s-u-boot.dtsi order
but keeping Orange Pi SPI flash bootph fragments.

--- a/arch/arm/dts/rk3588s-orangepi-5-u-boot.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/dts/rk3588s-orangepi-5-u-boot.dtsi
@@ -5,5 +5,5 @@
 
 / {
	chosen {
-		u-boot,spl-boot-order = "same-as-spl", &sdmmc;
+		u-boot,spl-boot-order = "same-as-spl", &sdhci, &sdmmc;
	};
 };
